# Vite env files. Vite auto-loads `.env`, `.env.local`, and the
# `.env.<mode>` variants at build time. `*.local` is the recommended
# place for per-developer values (like VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID for cloud
# backup) — never commit them.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
